Portugal, a signatory of the UN Kyoto Protocol, aims to generate 39% of its electricity from renewables like solar and wind power.
The country plans to construct the world's largest solar energy station in the Alentejo region, creating jobs and boosting the economy.
Solar power projects in the Philippines and Taiwan are also making strides, with Spain providing funding for rural villages.
Solar energy is gaining popularity globally, with companies like Blue Sun and Voltaic offering innovative solutions.
The future of solar power looks promising, especially with rising energy costs and government support.
